The Telegraph - Calcutta : Sports

 Climax asked to join camp 

OUR SPECIAL CORRESPONDENT

New Delhi: With Climax Lawrence yet to join the national camp, the All India Football Federation (AIFF) has finally woken up to act tough. According to sources, in a letter to the Dempo Sports Club on Wednesday, the AIFF has asked the footballer either to report to the camp or face disciplinary action . 

Rejecting Dempos offer to excuse the footballer from the camp because of injury, the federation general secretary said the matter should be left to the chief coach. Lawrence has been directed to join the camp with immediate effect. 

Lawrence has been regularly participating in the club practice and even playing in the Goa Professional League. 




